In this update:
[1] Haiti update
[2] Dominican Republic update
[3] PAHO update

******
[1] Haiti update
Date: Wed 22 Dec 2010
Source: Fox News [edited]
<http://www.myfoxny.com/dpps/news/haiti-cholera-toll-nears-2600-mark-dpgonc-20101222-gc_11184325>


Haiti's cholera death toll since the mid-October 2010 outbreak in the
impoverished Caribbean nation has reached 2591, official figures
showed Wednesday [22 Dec 2010].

Health ministry figures as of 17 Dec 2010, the most recent day
recorded, showed that 121 518 people have been treated for cholera.

At the outbreak's peak in November 2010, there were daily death tolls
of 80 and above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2] Dominican Republic update
Date: Thu 23 Dec 2010
Source: Dominican Today [edited]
<http://www.dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2010/12/2.3/38079/Most-of-the-82-people-with-cholera-totally-recovered-Public-Health-says>


Of the 82 people who have contracted cholera in the Dominican
Republic, 75 have totally recovered and are going about their daily
routine in different parts of the country.

The Public Health Ministry said Thursday [23 Dec 2010] that only 7
people are currently hospitalized and are in stable condition, with
their release expected by the weekend.

In a statement, Public Health added that as the result of the
intensive search by the National Epidemiology System, 9 more cases
were detected in 5 provinces.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

******
[3] PAHO Update
Date: Thu 23 Dec 2010
Source: PAHO [edited]
<http://new.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4577&Itemid=2206>


Weekly Update on the Cholera Situation as of EW 49 (5-11 Dec 2010)
-----------------------------------------
Currently, all 10 departments of Haiti have reported cases and deaths
due to cholera. During the previous 3 epidemiological weeks, the
highest cumulative incidence was observed in the departments of
Artibonite (305 cases per 10 000 inhabitants) followed by Nord Ouest,
Nord and Centre (with 190 and 185 and 167 cases per 10 000
inhabitants, respectively).

In the Dominican Republic, from EW 46 to EW 50, the Ministry of
Public Health of the Dominican Republic recorded 73 laboratory
confirmed cholera cases, of which 75 percent (55) were hospitalized.
No deaths were recorded. Also, 4 cases have been considered imported
and 69 autochthonous.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Marianne Hopp
